"script": "Right now, you're carrying about 38 trillion bacteria on and inside your body. That means microbes actually outnumber your own human cells. Scoop them all into a single pile, and they'd weigh roughly five pounds, about the size of your brain. You see, most of them live in your gut, helping you digest food and fight off invaders. And there are more bacteria in one spoonful of your insides than there are humans on the entire planet. So you're not really one creature at all, you're a walking city of trillions, and you'd quickly die without them.",
